        "**Practical tips**: Use a small learning rate (1e-5 – 5e-5), warm up the learning rate for\n",
        "the first 6–10% of steps, and apply weight decay to all parameters except biases and\n",
        "LayerNorm weights.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Instruction Tuning\n",
        "\n",
        "Instruction tuning fine-tunes a model on **(instruction, response)** pairs drawn from a wide\n",
        "variety of tasks, teaching the model to follow natural language commands zero-shot.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Prompt Format"
      ],
      "id": "0e77c036"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "def format_instruction_prompt(instruction: str, input_text: str = \"\",\n",
        "                               response: str = \"\") -> str:\n",
        "    parts = [f\"### Instruction:\\n{instruction}\"]\n",
        "    if input_text:\n",
        "        parts.append(f\"### Input:\\n{input_text}\")\n",
        "    parts.append(f\"### Response:\\n{response}\")\n",
        "    return \"\\n\\n\".join(parts)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "example = format_instruction_prompt(\n",
        "    instruction=\"Classify the sentiment of the following financial headline.\",\n",
        "    input_text=\"Apple reports record-breaking Q4 revenue.\",\n",
        "    response=\"POSITIVE\",\n",
        ")\n",
        "print(example)"
      ],
