        "Key datasets: FLAN (1,800 tasks), Alpaca (52k GPT-4-generated examples), Dolly, OpenAssistant.\n",
        "\n",
        "## RLHF: Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback\n",
        "\n",
        "RLHF (Ouyang et al., 2022) aligns a language model with human preferences through three stages:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Supervised Fine-Tuning (SFT)**: Fine-tune on demonstrations of the desired behaviour.\n",
        "2. **Reward Model**: Train a model to predict human preference scores from ranked output pairs.\n",
        "3. **PPO Optimisation**: Use Proximal Policy Optimization to maximise reward while a KL\n",
        "   penalty keeps the policy close to the SFT baseline.\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\mathcal{L}_\\text{PPO} = \\mathbb{E}\\!\\left[r(x,y) - \\beta \\cdot D_\\text{KL}(\\pi_\\theta \\,\\|\\, \\pi_\\text{SFT})\\right]$$\n",
        "\n",
        "**Alternative — DPO** (Rafailov et al., 2023): directly optimises a preference objective\n",
        "without a separate reward model, dramatically simplifying the training pipeline.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Parameter-Efficient Fine-Tuning (PEFT)\n",
        "\n",
        "### The Problem\n",
        "\n",
        "Full fine-tuning of a 7B-parameter model requires ~56 GB of GPU memory (fp16 + Adam states).\n",
        "PEFT methods freeze the pretrained weights and add a small number of trainable parameters.\n",
        "\n",
        "### LoRA: Low-Rank Adaptation\n",
        "\n",
        "LoRA (Hu et al., 2021) decomposes weight updates into low-rank matrices:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$W' = W + \\Delta W = W + B A$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where $B \\in \\mathbb{R}^{d \\times r}$, $A \\in \\mathbb{R}^{r \\times k}$, and $r \\ll \\min(d, k)$."
      ],
      "id": "6b363855"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "class LoRALinear(nn.Module):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Drop-in replacement for nn.Linear with LoRA adaptation.\"\"\"\n",
        "    def __init__(self, in_features: int, out_features: int,\n",
        "                 rank: int = 8, alpha: float = 16.0, dropout: float = 0.0):\n",
        "        super().__init__()\n",
        "        self.rank    = rank\n",
        "        self.alpha   = alpha\n",
        "        self.scaling = alpha / rank\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Frozen pretrained weight (no gradient)\n",
        "        self.weight  = nn.Parameter(torch.randn(out_features, in_features), requires_grad=False)\n",
        "        self.bias    = nn.Parameter(torch.zeros(out_features), requires_grad=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Trainable low-rank matrices\n",
        "        self.lora_A  = nn.Parameter(torch.randn(rank, in_features)  * (1 / rank)**0.5)\n",
        "        self.lora_B  = nn.Parameter(torch.zeros(out_features, rank))\n",
        "        self.dropout = nn.Dropout(dropout)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def forward(self, x: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:\n",
        "        base = F.linear(x, self.weight, self.bias)\n",
        "        lora = F.linear(self.dropout(x), self.lora_A)   # (B, T, rank)\n",
        "        lora = F.linear(lora, self.lora_B)               # (B, T, out)\n",
        "        return base + lora * self.scaling\n",
        "\n",
        "    def merge_weights(self) -> nn.Linear:\n",
        "        \"\"\"Fuse LoRA into the base weight for zero-latency inference.\"\"\"\n",
        "        merged = self.weight + (self.lora_B @ self.lora_A) * self.scaling\n",
        "        layer  = nn.Linear(self.weight.size(1), self.weight.size(0), bias=True)\n",
        "        layer.weight.data = merged\n",
        "        layer.bias.data   = self.bias.clone()\n",
        "        return layer\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Parameter count comparison\n",
        "d, k, r = 768, 768, 8\n",
        "full_params = d * k\n",
        "lora_params = r * (d + k)\n",
        "print(f\"Full weight: {full_params:,} params\")\n",
        "print(f\"LoRA (r={r}):  {lora_params:,} params  ({lora_params/full_params*100:.1f}%)\")"
